  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. I love the way you described food, so vivid! What's your favorite dish to cook at home?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I mostly cook simple things like pasta or dosa at home. My favorite is maybe paneer tikka. It’s tasty and I enjoy making it. Have you tried it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Paneer tikka sounds delicious. I get why you enjoy it, it's a favorite for many. What do you usually have it with, naan, roti, or something else?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Usually with naan, but sometimes I eat it with plain rice. It’s good both ways. Do you like spicy food?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Spicy food is fun! I like a little heat in my meals. How spicy do you like it, mild, medium, or something stronger?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I prefer medium spiciness, not too hot. But sometimes I add extra chili if I'm in the mood for a kick. My wife jokes that I love spicy food more than her. Pappu! 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Medium with a kick sounds perfect. A little playful banter with the wife adds to the fun, right? Pappu! What’s your go to spicy dish when you want that extra heat?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My go-to spicy dish is maybe vada pav with green chutney. Or sometimes a simple bhindi masala with a lot of green chili. Oh, and I love hot soup on cold days. Spicy soup is amaazing. 🌶️"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Vada pav and bhindi masala, both are spicy classics! Hot soup on a cold day sounds comforting. Do you have a favorite type of soup you like to make?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like tomato soup with a bit of cream and spices. Sometimes I make it with ajwain for that extra kick. But honestly, any spicy soup warms me up on a cold day. Have you tried it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Tomato soup with ajwain sounds tasty, a nice mix of warmth and spice. I can imagine it’s perfect for cold evenings. Do you make it often during winters?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I make it quite often in winters, especially after coming back from work. It’s quick and gives that instant comfort. Sometimes I even add a dash of jeera for more flavor. You know, it’s like a small treat for yourself after a long day. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Quick comfort after a long day makes all the difference. Jeera adds such a nice hint, clever touch! What’s your favorite comfort food on busy days?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "On busy days, I often go for something quick like poha or upma. They’re easy to make and ready in 10 mins. Sometimes I add some veggies or eggs to make it more filling. It’s not fancy, but it works."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Poha or upma in 10 minutes, efficiency and taste in one dish! Adding veggies or eggs makes it perfect. What’s your go to snack when you need something even quicker?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My go-to quick snack is bhujia or some pakoras if I have veggies on hand. If I’m really in a rush, a banana or some nuts will do. I also keep some roasted chana in the pantry for those \"I need something now\" moments."
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Bhujia, pakoras, or roasted chana, you’ve covered all the bases! It’s smart to have quick snacks ready. What’s your favorite to munch on while watching a movie?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually go for popcorn, obviously! But if I’m in the mood for something salty, I’ll have some namkeen or roasted peanuts. Sometimes I even make sweet popcorn with a bit of jaggery — it’s a Bollywood movie staple for me. 🍿"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Popcorn and namkeen, the perfect movie duo! Sweet popcorn with jaggery sounds like a Bollywood treat. Do you have a favorite film to watch with it?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge is a classic for me, or maybe Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara for something more energetic. But honestly, any movie with good music works — it’s all about the snacks and the vibe! 🎬"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Dilwale and Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara, both great picks for snacks and music! What song from either film do you find yourself humming the most?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I always hum \"Mehbooba Mehbooba\" from DDLJ — it’s so iconic! Or \"Zindagi\" from ZNMD when I’m feeling adventurous. Music and snacks make even an ordinary day feel like a festival, you know? 🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Mehbooba Mehbooba and Zindagi, both songs set the mood perfectly! Music really brings snacks to life. What’s your favorite song to play when you’re cooking?\""
    }
  ],
